# Web3Forms access key — used CLIENT-SIDE. The form submits straight to Web3Forms
# from the browser (their endpoint is browser-only, behind Cloudflare), so the key
# needs the NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix to be available in the browser bundle.
#
# This key is PUBLIC BY DESIGN — it only lets a message be dropped into the Web3Forms
# account; it reveals nothing. The email it routes to is stored on Web3Forms' side and
# never appears in the code or on the page.
#
# Get a key at https://web3forms.com (enter your real email — that's where messages land).
# Local dev:  copy this file to .env.local and fill in the key.
# Production:  add the same variable in Vercel -> Project Settings -> Environment Variables.
# Recommended after deploy: turn on Domain Restriction in Web3Forms settings so the key
# only works from your live domain (stops anyone reusing it elsewhere).
NEXT_PUBLIC_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY=
